        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Erwin Edelman (b. 1928?) was a progressive activist, possibly a one-time member of the Communist Party USA, and the author of the unpublished typescript "The Suppressed Facts of the Rosenberg Case."</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>This collection contains a 142 page undated typescript, "The Suppressed Facts of the Rosenberg Case," by Erwin Edelman. This critique of the United States government's case against Julius and Ethel Rosenberg, who were convicted in 1951, then executed in 1953, for allegedly conspiring to commit espionage to give information to the Soviet Union on the construction of U.S. atomic bombs, focuses on the problematic notion of the existence of an "atomic bomb secret." This manuscript was originally in the papers of one-time Communists Earl and Sylvia Price (TAM 175). PLEASE DIRECT FURTHER INQUIRIES TO: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
        </scopecontent>
